{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow up to 10 days authorised school leave per year without fines",
        "additional_details": "Many families cannot afford holidays during official school holidays due to significantly increased prices. Some children, particularly those with SEND, can struggle with busy peak travel periods due to crowds and sensory challenges. We do not think that parents should face fines or court action when a child\u2019s attendance is otherwise excellent and their education is not affected. A fairer system could support both education and family wellbeing.",
        "background": "Introduce national school attendance rules to allow parents to take children out of school for up to 10 days per year for family leave where attendance is otherwise good, including flexibility for families with children with SEND, without fines or prosecution.",
        "closed_at": null,
